results.title: The Starry Night (1889) by Vincent Van Gogh (Longsleeve)
results.description: The Starry Night is an oil on canvas painting by Dutch Post-Impressionist painter Vincent van Gogh. Painted in June 1889, it depicts the view from the east-facing window of his asylum room at Saint-Rémy-de-Provence, just before sunrise, with the addition of an imaginary village. It has been in the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York City since 1941, acquired through the Lillie P. Bliss Bequest. Widely regarded as Van Gogh's magnum opus, The Starry Night is one of the most recognized paintings in Western art.

results.title: German Gift Sign Live Well Laugh Often Love Much Rustic Vintage Shabby Chic Sign Extra Large
results.description:
Last Date For Orders For Guaranteed Christmas Delivery is 	
Sunday 9th December. Please order by this date. Inspirational Words Painted On Wood In German! (The essence of the translation = Live well Laugh often Love much)

What a truly original gift this would make!

This piece measure 28 inches long x 4 inches high (71cm x 10cm) A wonderful size for displaying above a door, on a door, amidst a wall display or gently resting on a shelf or mantle - the possibilities are endless.

My work is collected widely and grace all room and garden settings.

All my pieces are painted with great love and care by me - no mass produced cookie cutting process here - It's just me and a huge passion for creating truly beautiful art signs with some amazing words.

Layers of paint, wax and by beautiful letter work are applied over a number of days, each piece is then gently distressed capturing the illusion that it has fallen out of a long long time ago - positively vintage!

Finally the entire piece is sealed for indoor and outdoor use and a hanger attached so that it is ready to hang as soon as it is unwrapped!

No two pieces of my work are ever the same - The wood grain, knots, notches, wood shakes all differ to give each piece a true uniqueness - every piece receives my high level of attention to detail - my work is intended to live for a very long time indeed!

A great choice of gentle colours all with a coal underlay apart from the vintage cream which rests far more beautifully over a cocoa underlay.

Thanks so much for looking and please take a peep at my store front to read about the story of my art signs and their "journey" from a piece of bare timber to an art sign that is a privilege to have created.

delivery:
Your order will be gently and carefully made over a number of days (sometimes up to 10 to 14 days to make  - due to layers of paint, wax and seals!) and will be sent out with a secure signed for and fully trackable courier delivery service.
